descript.abstract: This dataset contains the Designated Stocked Trout Waters (Catchable Trout Stocking Program) in Virginia for public use. While many of these locations are lakes, reservoirs, or ponds, some may represent single stocking locations on streams. These data are formatted as an ArcView shapefile and were compiled by the Virginia Department of Game and Inland Fisheries (VDGIF). These data are presented as points. Rainbow, Brown, and Brook Trout represent the species being stocked. This data does not supercede physical signage at the locations indicated. This data is to be used as a guide, not for official use, and this data is not considered to be an official boundary of the stocked trout waters.
descript.purpose: To show locations for publicly accessible trout fishing based on VDGIF stocking.

dataqual.complete: No warranty, expressed or implied, is made regarding the accuracy, adequacy, completeness, reliability, or usefulness of any data provided. These data are provided on an "as is" basis. All warranties of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to fitness for a particular use, freedom from computer viruses, and non-infringement of proprietary rights, are disclaimed. Data are added and changed periodically, and data may become out-of-date quickly. It is recommended that the user not let a significant period of time elapse between obtaining and using the data. Data was comprised using the most current reports of VDGIF biologists . These listings are subject to frequent and unanounced changes, which may affect stocking status.

procstep.procdesc: GPS coordinates were provided by VDGIF field biologists. Points do not represent centroids of lakes, or public access points. They are simply a location point for the lake and should not be replied upon for accuracy. The data was then confirmed by the biologists as accurate, and attribute data was provided by the biologists. The trout stocking regulations from VDGIF were also used to verify attribute accuracy.

attrdomv.udom: Sequential unique whole numbers that are automatically generated.

attr.attrdef: Trout stocking designation. Put and Take (PNT), Delayed Harvest (DH), Special Regulations (SR), Feefishing (FF), Urban (U).
County where the majority of the feature is located.
Notes from the biologists and fishing regulations.
Brook trout stocked. Y = Stocked. M = May be stocked. Null = Not stocked. %s = percent of the total stocked trout.
Rainbow trout stocked. Y = Stocked. M = May be stocked. Null = Not stocked. %s = percent of the total stocked trout.
Brown trout stocked. Y = Stocked. M = May be stocked. Null = Not stocked. %s = percent of the total stocked trout.
Trout stocking category. A = stocked 8 times between October 1 and May 30. B = 5 times. C = 3 times.
If the reach is a Heritage Day water. http://www.dgif.virginia.gov/fishing/trout/trout-heritage-day/
If the reach lies within a National Forest. National Forest permit required.

overview.dsoverv: This dataset gives spatial representation to the streams listed in the 2011 Virginia Fishing Regulations. Please refer to these regulations for detailed information concerning regulations, stocking information, access, and more. The comments field does not include all of the regulations which apply to the listed waterbodies.
